parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering can cause the vehicle to become difficult to steer, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when turning or merging at low speeds.
symptoms: The power steering fails or becomes intermittent
making it hard to turn the steering wheel
especially at low speeds; the steering wheel locks or becomes difficult to turn; a loud noise or hum is heard when turning; the power steering fluid level is low or leaking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering rack and pinion can cause the vehicle to become difficult to steer, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when turning or merging at low speeds.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
especially at low speeds; the steering rack and pinion leak fluid; a loud noise or grinding sound is heard when turning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain can cause the engine to fail, leading to a loss of power and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine light comes on; the timing chain stretches or fails; the crankshaft is warped or damaged; the engine needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain can cause the engine to stall or seize, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The check engine light comes on
the vehicle hesitates or stalls while accelerating
the engine makes a rattling or ticking noise
the vehicle loses power
the engine seizes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine oil pump can cause the engine to seize, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine seizes
the check engine light comes on
the vehicle loses power
the engine makes a loud noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioner hose can cause the engine to overheat, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The air conditioner hose melts or ruptures
the engine overheats
the vehicle loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain can cause the engine to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The check engine light illuminates
the engine hesitates or loses power
the vehicle stalls or dies
the timing chain stretches or breaks
and the engine may suffer significant damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission problems can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle loses power or acceleration
the engine RPMs surge or drop
the transmission warning light illuminates
and the vehicle may stall or die.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cruise control and brake issues can cause the vehicle to lose control or accelerate unexpectedly, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The cruise control does not disengage when the clutch pedal is depressed
the vehicle rolls backward on an incline
the brakes feel spongy or unresponsive
and the vehicle may accelerate unexpectedly.
